      "content": "You should look for a triple-antibiotic ointment, the kind with Neomycin, Bacitracin, and Polymyxin B, as these cover the most common culprits. Apply a thin layer of this ointment directly onto the wound site, making sure it covers the entire area of the incision. Do this three to four times a day, especially after you've gently cleaned the area with saline solution. This regimen will keep the microbes in check and promote a swift, clean healing process.",
